  "texts": [
    "This risk is then passed through an MLP to yield a 2D feature vector z, which a softmax layer normalizes to ŷ.",
    "The groundtruth label for ŷ is given by y and is computed through (8c)i d = µ θ + σ θ • i ϵ, i ϵ ∼ N (0, 1), ∀i = 1,..., N (8a) i h( i d) = -i d + do, i h( i d) = max(0, i h( i d)) (8b) y = [0, 1] T, if -dgt + do ≤ 0 [1, 0] T, if -dgt + do > 0 (8c) L = LN LL + LCE, LCE = -y T log(ŷ)(8d)The architecture of Fig. 5 is trained with a combination of NLL and a cross-entropy loss (8d).",
    "The latter acts as an implicit task-aware regularization on the predicted σ θ (u, o).",
    "F. Overall ApproachAlg.",
    "1 presents our overall approach wherein we solve (1a)-(1b) using the trained neural worst-case obstacle clearance model as our collision predictor."
